  "response": "Here are two highly recommended books about Swami Vivekananda:\n\n1. \"Swami Vivekananda: A Biography\" by Nivedita Ramakrishna\n- Written by Sister Nivedita, a direct disciple of Swami Vivekananda\n- Provides an intimate and authentic account of his life\n- Covers his spiritual journey, philosophical teachings, and social work\n\n2. \"The Complete Works of Swami Vivekananda\" (9 Volumes)\n- Compiled and published by Advaita Ashrama\n- Contains Swami Vivekananda's speeches, writings, letters, and conversations\n- Offers comprehensive insights into his philosophy, thoughts on religion, nationalism, and social issues\n\nBoth books are excellent resources to understand Swami Vivekananda's life, philosophy, and contributions to Indian renaissance and global spirituality. The first book provides a biographical narrative, while the second offers a deep dive into his actual writings and thoughts.\n\nIf you're looking for a more concise introduction, \"Swami Vivekananda: A Biography\" would be the recommended choice. For an in-depth study, \"The Complete Works\" is an invaluable resource.",
